---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = 'How Nubo Works | One Timeline, Easy Logging';
const description = 'See how Nubo combines a physical baby tracker device, free app, voice catch-up, caregiver sync, and Alexa logging into one baby timeline.';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  name: title,
  description,
  url: 'https://www.nubotracker.com/how-it-works/',
  about: { '@type': 'Product', name: 'Nubo Baby Tracker' }
};
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} jsonLd={jsonLd}>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="overline">How it works</p>
        <h1>One baby timeline. Use what is easiest in the moment.</h1>
        <p class="page-hero-sub">Press a button, speak a sentence, tap a card, or ask Alexa. Everything lands in one timeline that caregivers can trust.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="methods-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="method-grid">
          <article><img src="/images/nubo-device-hand.webp" alt="Hand pressing the Nubo tracker device" width="640" height="400" /><h2>Tap the device</h2><p>The fastest log when your phone is locked, across the room, or too bright for 3 a.m.</p></article>
          <article><img src="/images/appscreens/02_voicelogging.webp" alt="Nubo app voice logging screen" width="642" height="1389" /><h2>Say it on your phone</h2><p>Catch up later with natural language and the right historical timestamp.</p></article>
          <article><img src="/images/appscreens/01_onetouch.webp" alt="Nubo app one-touch cards" width="642" height="1389" /><h2>Tap a card</h2><p>When the phone is open, quick cards make common logs fast and structured.</p></article>
          <article><img src="/images/nubo-alexa-echo-show.webp" alt="Nubo dashboard on an Amazon Echo Show" width="640" height="400" /><h2>Ask Alexa</h2><p>Log from across the room when your hands are busy with bottles, laundry, or baby.</p></article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="day-section">
      <div class="container day-inner">
        <div>
          <p class="overline">A day in the life</p>
          <h2>Different caregivers. Different moments. One record.</h2>
          <p>The point is not to force one habit. The point is to make the next log easy enough that it actually happens.</p>
        </div>
        <ol class="timeline">
          <li><time>5:47 a.m.</time><span>Mom feeds baby half-asleep and taps the device.</span></li>
          <li><time>7:15 a.m.</time><span>Dad takes over and taps a card in the app while making coffee.</span></li>
          <li><time>11:00 a.m.</time><span>Nanny arrives and presses the device through the day.</span></li>
          <li><time>2:30 p.m.</time><span>Mom checks the lock-screen activity from work.</span></li>
          <li><time>6:30 p.m.</time><span>Grandma uses Alexa to log a bottle from across the room.</span></li>
          <li><time>11:00 p.m.</time><span>Dad says "she had 4 ounces around 9" and Nubo catches up.</span></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="setup-section">
      <div class="container setup-inner">
        <img src="/images/care_with_confidence.webp" alt="Nubo app, device, and caregivers staying in sync" width="1536" height="651" />
        <div>
          <p class="overline">Setup flow</p>
          <h2>Pair in about 30 seconds. Invite caregivers with a QR code.</h2>
          <p>Start with the free app. Add the device when nighttime feeds, hands-full care, or multi-caregiver handoffs start to dominate.</p>
          <div class="hero-actions-inline"><a href="/device/" class="btn-primary">View the device</a><a href="/pricing/" class="btn-ghost">See pricing</a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .methods-section, .day-section, .setup-section { padding: 6rem 0; }
  .methods-section, .setup-section { background: #fff; }
  .day-section { background: var(--color-bg-soft); }
  .method-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 1.5rem; }
  .method-grid article { background: var(--color-bg-soft); border-radius: var(--radius-xl); padding: 1rem 1rem 1.5rem; text-align: center; }
  .method-grid img { width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 4 / 3; object-fit: cover; object-position: top; border-radius: 18px; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .method-grid h2 { font-size: 1.125rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .method-grid p, .day-inner p, .timeline span, .setup-inner p { color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.7; }
  .day-inner, .setup-inner { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 0.9fr 1.1fr; gap: 4rem; align-items: center; }
  .day-inner h2, .setup-inner h2 { font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 3rem); line-height: 1.12; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .timeline { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
  .timeline li { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 6rem 1fr; gap: 1rem; background: #fff; border-radius: 16px; padding: 1rem; }
  .timeline time { font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-brand-dark); }
  .setup-inner img { border-radius: var(--radius-xl); box-shadow: 0 20px 50px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08); }
  .hero-actions-inline { display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  @media (max-width: 980px) { .method-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } .day-inner, .setup-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .methods-section, .day-section, .setup-section { padding: 4rem 0; } .method-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .timeline li { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.25rem; } }
</style>